<section id="about" class="py-16 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
    <!-- Left: Text (3/5) -->
    <div class="lg:col-span-3">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">// ABOUT</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#FAFAFA] mb-6 leading-tight">
        Engineer who cares about<br class="hidden md:block" /> the 2am call
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4 text-[#A1A1AA] leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Three years deep in DevOps and platform engineering, with a focus on observability and
          making on-call shifts survivable. I've built and shipped production systems across AWS, Azure,
          and GCP — but the work I care about most is the infrastructure that makes other engineers faster.
        </p>
        <p>
          At Sitecore (via IGT1 Lanka), I led the rollout of the full Grafana LGTM stack — Loki,
          Grafana, Tempo, Mimir, and Pyroscope — across 20+ microservices. I also shipped Project
          UNITE, an internal developer platform on Backstage that cut onboarding time by 40% and
          killed 80% of "where is X?" Slack threads.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before that, I taught DevOps at YARL IT Hub, designing a curriculum from scratch and
          watching 30+ students land SRE/DevOps roles. Still mentor school students on weekends —
          it keeps me honest about what actually matters vs. what just sounds good on a dashboard.
        </p>
        <p>
          Looking for remote roles with modern teams that care about developer experience, system
          reliability, and real ownership. Not just tickets.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stats -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-[#27272A] bg-[#111111]">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#3B82F6]">3+</p>
